WEBVTT

00:05.965 --> 00:07.967
♪ ♪

00:13.973 --> 00:15.975
[laughter]

00:17.017 --> 00:19.061
Cake! Cake! Cake! Cake! Cake!

00:19.145 --> 00:21.397
[Belly] Every birthday
I've ever had has been here,

00:21.480 --> 00:23.315
in this house.

00:23.399 --> 00:26.277
[all] ♪ Cha, cha, cha,
happy birthday...

00:26.360 --> 00:28.195
[Belly] It's always the same.

00:28.279 --> 00:30.114
Mom makes me
Mickey Mouse pancakes.

00:30.197 --> 00:32.741
Everyone gives me presents.

00:32.825 --> 00:35.035
[all] ♪ Dear Belly...

00:35.119 --> 00:36.495
[Belly] It's the one day
the boys

00:36.579 --> 00:39.331
have to include me
in everything.

00:39.415 --> 00:41.041
It's my favorite day
of the year.

00:41.125 --> 00:42.668
[cheering and applause]

00:42.752 --> 00:44.670
[laughter]

00:44.754 --> 00:46.797
[cheering]

00:48.924 --> 00:51.427
[laughter]

00:56.015 --> 00:58.058
- What is that?
- Infinity.

00:58.142 --> 01:00.644
Do you know what that means?

01:00.728 --> 01:03.647
It's really cool.
I learned it in math class.

01:03.731 --> 01:07.860
So, you know how numbers
keep getting bigger and bigger?

01:07.943 --> 01:09.570
A hundred, a thousand,
a million.

01:09.653 --> 01:11.322
To get to the biggest number
in the world,

01:11.405 --> 01:12.782
you'd have to keep counting

01:12.865 --> 01:15.326
because there's always
a bigger number.

01:15.409 --> 01:17.328
It's boundless.

01:17.411 --> 01:18.579
I don't get it.

01:19.747 --> 01:22.333
Imagine it's a racetrack.

01:22.416 --> 01:25.169
You see how there's
no starting or ending point?

01:25.252 --> 01:28.506
You could travel endlessly
around those curves.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.174
Goes on forever.

01:30.257 --> 01:32.301
That's infinity.

01:35.971 --> 01:39.015
♪ ♪

01:39.098 --> 01:41.352
[sighs]

01:54.782 --> 01:56.991
[indistinct conversation]

01:57.076 --> 01:58.369
[Steven] Golden brown and crisp.

01:58.452 --> 01:59.370
That's how it's
supposed to look.

01:59.453 --> 02:00.454
[Laurel] How's it
going over there?

02:00.538 --> 02:01.997
- Look at these pancakes.
- It's ready.

02:02.081 --> 02:03.374
[Belly] Morning, everyone.

02:03.457 --> 02:04.542
- Happy birthday.
- Hey!

02:04.625 --> 02:05.793
[laughs]

02:05.876 --> 02:07.545
There's the birthday girl,

02:07.628 --> 02:09.463
looking like a vision in floral.

02:09.547 --> 02:10.840
Happy birthday.

02:10.923 --> 02:12.633
- [laughs]
- Happy sweet 16, Bells.

02:12.716 --> 02:14.844
Now Belly Button's
getting old finally.

02:14.927 --> 02:17.179
- Happy birthday.
- Thanks, everyone.

02:17.263 --> 02:19.431
- Happy birthday, sweetheart.
- Thanks, Mom.

02:19.515 --> 02:21.851
Your Mickey Mouse pancakes
are ready.

02:21.934 --> 02:24.353
Actually, I'm not really,
uh, hungry.

02:24.436 --> 02:26.105
Oh.

02:26.188 --> 02:27.523
Shall we open gifts?

02:27.606 --> 02:29.900
Oh, you're gonna love mine.

02:32.027 --> 02:34.655
♪ ♪

02:41.161 --> 02:42.454
[Laurel] It's a first edition.

02:42.538 --> 02:44.206
I got it from
a rare book dealer.

02:44.290 --> 02:45.833
Thanks, Mom.

02:45.916 --> 02:47.543
Turn to the bookmarked page.

02:48.711 --> 02:50.880
- It's your favorite poem.
- [Belly] Oh, yeah.

02:50.963 --> 02:53.007
I remember Susannah
teaching us to recite this.

02:53.090 --> 02:54.966
"For whatever we lose...

02:55.050 --> 02:57.177
[Jeremiah and Belly] Like a you
or a me

02:57.261 --> 02:59.555
[all] It's always
ourselves we find

02:59.638 --> 03:01.181
- in the sea."
- [chuckles]

03:01.265 --> 03:02.892
Thank you. I love it.

03:02.975 --> 03:04.643
You're welcome.

03:04.727 --> 03:06.604
Okay, open mine now, Belly.

03:08.564 --> 03:10.482
[wrapping paper tearing]

03:11.775 --> 03:14.194
♪ ♪

03:15.487 --> 03:17.281
[Belly] Oh, wow.

03:17.364 --> 03:19.033
They're gorgeous.
Thank you, Susannah.

03:22.119 --> 03:25.331
My mom gave me these pearls

03:25.414 --> 03:27.875
for my sweet 16.

03:32.713 --> 03:35.215
Radiant, isn't she?

03:35.299 --> 03:37.259
They look great on you,
sweetheart.

03:38.844 --> 03:40.054
Oh, I'm next.

03:40.137 --> 03:41.972
- [Jeremiah] Here.
- [Belly laughs] Thank you.

03:46.477 --> 03:49.396
It's a good-luck charm to help
you pass your driving test.

03:50.856 --> 03:53.400
- [Jeremiah laughs]
- Perfect.

03:53.484 --> 03:54.652
Thank you.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.862
- Think fast, Belly.
- What?

03:56.946 --> 03:58.197
[Laurel] Steven.

03:59.781 --> 04:02.451
Wow, Steven, I can't believe
you actually

04:02.534 --> 04:04.078
- spent money on me.
- [Steven] Relax.

04:04.161 --> 04:06.372
I just didn't want you stealing
mine next year when I get in.

04:06.455 --> 04:08.415
I didn't know you were
still considering Princeton.

04:08.499 --> 04:11.335
You know, I-I think I'm gonna
apply for some scholarships,

04:11.418 --> 04:12.920
and Dad thinks I can get
some financial aid.

04:13.003 --> 04:14.296
I-I don't know.
I'll see if I get in.

04:14.380 --> 04:16.798
Okay. Um...

04:16.882 --> 04:20.511
Conrad, uh, do you want
to give Belly your present?

04:24.264 --> 04:26.308
Sorry, I forgot.

04:26.392 --> 04:30.104
[♪ Alessia Cara:
"You Let Me Down"]

04:30.187 --> 04:33.607
Uh, that's... that's cool. Um...

04:33.691 --> 04:37.277
I wasn't really expecting
anything anyway, so...

04:39.697 --> 04:42.157
Oh, so I got to go.
Um, I promised Cleveland

04:42.241 --> 04:45.284
that I'd show him
some knots today, so...

04:48.747 --> 04:50.541
Happy birthday, Belly.

04:51.750 --> 04:53.711
[door opens]

04:53.794 --> 04:57.214
Hey. Why don't we take my car
and practice driving

04:57.297 --> 04:59.091
before we have to pick up Taylor
from the bus station.

04:59.174 --> 05:01.093
♪ The last time...

05:01.176 --> 05:02.761
Sure.

05:07.057 --> 05:08.726
[Jeremiah] Okay, slow and
steady. You're doing great.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.477
Just keep going straight, okay?

05:10.561 --> 05:11.645
Okay.

05:11.729 --> 05:13.897
You excited to see Taylor?

05:13.981 --> 05:17.401
Yeah, uh, of course. So excited.

05:17.484 --> 05:20.529
You sure? [chuckles]

05:20.612 --> 05:22.990
Look, she's my best friend
in the world,

05:23.073 --> 05:25.576
but, um, I mean,
you know how Taylor is.

05:25.659 --> 05:28.120
She's like a hurricane.

05:28.203 --> 05:29.747
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Hurricane Taylor.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.040
[both laugh]

05:31.123 --> 05:34.001
And I guess I always

05:34.084 --> 05:36.211
feel like the supporting
character around her,

05:36.295 --> 05:37.880
which, normally, I don't mind.

05:37.963 --> 05:39.882
But it's your birthday,

05:39.965 --> 05:41.925
and you're the main character,
Belly, not her.

05:42.009 --> 05:44.511
Yeah. Thanks, Jere.

05:44.595 --> 05:46.346
♪ To myself...

05:46.430 --> 05:47.765
[tires screech]

05:47.848 --> 05:49.516
[exhales]

05:49.600 --> 05:52.603
- Whoops.
- [chuckles] Bells?

05:52.686 --> 05:54.855
We're gonna need a part two
to this driving lesson, okay?

05:54.938 --> 05:56.982
And part three and part four.

05:57.066 --> 05:59.234
[both laugh]

05:59.318 --> 06:03.072
♪ I love you,
but you let me down ♪♪

06:03.155 --> 06:05.157
All right, just picture it
like this, okay?

06:05.240 --> 06:08.327
This standing line is the tree,
and all you have to do

06:08.410 --> 06:11.371
is make a loop for the
rabbit hole, and the rabbit

06:11.455 --> 06:12.790
comes out of the hole,

06:12.873 --> 06:15.209
around the back of the tree,
back down the hole.

06:16.752 --> 06:18.295
You got yourself a bowline knot.

06:18.378 --> 06:19.922
[laughing]

06:21.298 --> 06:23.842
That is one of the most
convoluted metaphors

06:23.926 --> 06:25.385
I have ever encountered.

06:25.469 --> 06:27.262
Yeah, I guess
growing up around it,

06:27.346 --> 06:29.431
I never really thought about
how weird it might sound, but...

06:29.515 --> 06:30.474
No, no, no.

06:30.557 --> 06:33.102
So, um...

06:33.185 --> 06:36.230
They're doing this, um,
segment with me for

06:36.313 --> 06:38.524
the Good Morning Massachusetts
show this afternoon.

06:38.607 --> 06:40.567
Ha, ha. And, uh,

06:40.651 --> 06:43.320
could you come early
and help me prep?

06:43.403 --> 06:44.738
You know, I do not want

06:44.822 --> 06:46.615
to get canceled
by the sailing community.

06:46.698 --> 06:47.783
- [laughs]
- So...

06:47.866 --> 06:49.993
Yeah, no, yeah, I'd be,
I'd be, I'd be happy to.

06:50.077 --> 06:52.454
Great. I look forward
to sounding like

06:52.538 --> 06:54.248
I know what
I'm talking about. [laughs]

06:54.331 --> 06:56.375
- It's rabbits and trees, man.
- [laughs]

06:56.457 --> 06:57.709
All right, let's get back to it.

06:57.793 --> 06:58.710
- Uh...
- Right, man.

06:58.794 --> 07:00.087
- Show me what you got.
- Tree.

07:00.170 --> 07:02.631
- Rabbit.
- Yeah.

07:02.714 --> 07:04.508
[Steven] Mmm.

07:04.591 --> 07:06.718
Thank you. Thank you.

07:06.802 --> 07:08.554
Okay, so I know
it's a little bit extra

07:08.637 --> 07:10.931
to go all the way to New York
just for dress fittings,

07:11.014 --> 07:12.641
but this designer, Olivia Lim,

07:12.724 --> 07:14.643
I'm trying to work with,
she's amazing.

07:14.726 --> 07:16.478
She just graduated
from Central Saint Martins

07:16.562 --> 07:19.148
in London last summer,
and she's just been blowing up.

07:19.231 --> 07:21.859
Yeah. Yeah, no, I-I think
I've actually heard about her.

07:21.942 --> 07:25.195
And, oh, my gosh, her studio
in Chinatown is so cool.

07:25.279 --> 07:27.072
She hands you Pocky
and champagne in a can

07:27.156 --> 07:28.490
the minute you walk in.

07:28.574 --> 07:31.743
Whoa. Getting customers buzzed
on-on sugar and booze,

07:31.827 --> 07:34.204
- that's the move. [laughs]
- Yeah. That's what I'm saying.

07:34.288 --> 07:36.039
And if you look
at her Instagram,

07:36.123 --> 07:37.499
she has some menswear options

07:37.582 --> 07:40.210
that might go really nicely with
what I'm planning on wearing.

07:40.294 --> 07:41.670
Here.

07:47.634 --> 07:49.761
Oh.

07:49.845 --> 07:51.221
Yeah.

07:52.764 --> 07:55.933
I mean, yeah. Yeah, no, I mean,
those look, those look great.

07:56.018 --> 07:57.811
We, like, totally don't have to
coordinate outfits

07:57.895 --> 08:00.063
- if you don't want to.
It's fine.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

08:00.147 --> 08:01.064
I-I want to.

08:01.148 --> 08:02.691
Geez, I'm sorry.

08:02.774 --> 08:04.318
No, I really, really want to.

08:04.401 --> 08:05.861
I mean, honestly, you're, like,

08:05.944 --> 08:07.321
the best-dressed girl
in Cousins.

08:08.572 --> 08:11.325
It's, um... not that hard.

08:11.408 --> 08:14.453
[both laugh]

08:16.830 --> 08:19.082
Look, um...

08:19.166 --> 08:21.668
I just really want
to look good next to you.

08:21.752 --> 08:23.670
You will.

08:25.797 --> 08:27.716
You do.

08:35.349 --> 08:37.100
- [chuckles]
- Twenty bucks she calls you
"Jeremy" again.

08:37.183 --> 08:39.227
- I don't... I think
she learned from last time.
- You think?

08:39.311 --> 08:41.313
That's how she flirts with you.

08:42.356 --> 08:45.025
- Here she comes.
- [gasps]

08:45.108 --> 08:47.361
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
- [giggling]

08:47.444 --> 08:49.821
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

08:49.905 --> 08:51.281
Belly, you little tart.

08:51.365 --> 08:52.449
[Belly] What?

08:52.532 --> 08:53.575
You finally took my advice.

08:53.659 --> 08:54.826
This outfit is snatched.

08:54.910 --> 08:56.536
[laughing] Oh, my God, Taylor.

08:56.620 --> 08:57.621
Isn't Belly
looking like a snack?

08:57.704 --> 08:59.081
Always.

08:59.164 --> 09:00.290
Thank you.

09:00.374 --> 09:02.542
Oh, uh, here,
let me get your bag.

09:02.626 --> 09:04.378
Thank you.
You're such a gentleman, Jeremy.

09:04.461 --> 09:06.004
- Of course.
- [Belly] Um...

09:06.088 --> 09:09.216
- It's Jeremiah, not Jeremy.
- I like "Jeremy" better.

09:09.299 --> 09:11.260
- [Belly chuckles]
- Uh, should we, uh, head home?

09:11.343 --> 09:13.887
Ooh, actually,
can we make a stop first?

09:13.971 --> 09:15.305
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

09:16.974 --> 09:17.975
[Jeremiah] Wow.

09:19.601 --> 09:21.186
Mmm. I live.

09:21.270 --> 09:23.021
I would literally eat this
every day if I could.

09:23.105 --> 09:24.189
[Belly] Me, too.

09:24.273 --> 09:26.233
Mmm.

09:26.316 --> 09:27.359
Okay.

09:28.860 --> 09:30.112
Open your present.

09:34.658 --> 09:37.286
I think it'll look
so hot on you.

09:37.369 --> 09:39.329
- [Jeremiah chuckles]
- Do you like it?

09:39.413 --> 09:40.831
Okay, Belly would never
wear that. [laughs]

09:40.914 --> 09:43.500
Actually, I really like it.

09:43.583 --> 09:44.710
Thank you, Taylor.

09:44.793 --> 09:46.253
You're welcome.

09:46.336 --> 09:49.006
Okay, so, what's the plan
for tonight? Where's the party?

09:49.089 --> 09:51.675
Well, Susannah always plans
a big lobster dinner.

09:51.758 --> 09:53.051
Boring. No.

09:53.135 --> 09:56.680
It's your 16th birthday.
We have to go out.

09:56.763 --> 09:59.141
No, no, no. These dinners
are really, really fun.

09:59.224 --> 10:02.144
And Susannah had the idea
to make it Midsommar themed,

10:02.227 --> 10:03.603
so she got flower crowns

10:03.687 --> 10:04.938
especially made for us
and everything.

10:05.022 --> 10:06.356
Don't you think
you should be spending

10:06.440 --> 10:07.691
your birthday
with people your own age?

10:07.774 --> 10:09.276
I am. You're here.

10:09.359 --> 10:10.527
Hello? Am I invisible?

10:10.610 --> 10:11.653
And I guess Steven.

10:11.737 --> 10:12.654
[scoffs]

10:12.738 --> 10:14.531
And Cam's coming, too.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.950
Yay, I'm so excited to meet
the guy who finally got you

10:17.034 --> 10:18.368
to take your eyes off
of you-know-who.

10:18.452 --> 10:19.870
- Taylor.
- What?

10:22.581 --> 10:23.749
I have an idea.

10:23.832 --> 10:25.083
We can go to Nicole's
big blowout

10:25.167 --> 10:27.127
at her place tonight.
Maybe go after dinner?

10:27.210 --> 10:29.212
Yes. Who's Nicole?

10:29.296 --> 10:30.839
She's my big sister
for the deb ball.

10:30.922 --> 10:34.551
She's super nice and just
really cool and fun and...

10:34.634 --> 10:37.012
Ugh, I'm, like,
melting right now.

10:37.095 --> 10:38.472
Can we go back to the house?

10:38.555 --> 10:40.307
I want to change into my bikini
and jump in the pool.

10:40.390 --> 10:41.975
Sure.

10:42.059 --> 10:43.393
- I call shotgun.
- Come on, Bells.

10:43.477 --> 10:45.020
♪ ♪

10:45.103 --> 10:46.813
Okay. Hold on.

10:46.897 --> 10:49.066
I'm coming.

10:49.149 --> 10:51.485
[Taylor] Oh, wow.
Look who decided to be nice.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.697
- [laughs]
- Yeah.

10:55.781 --> 10:57.407
[Taylor] Conrad is going to lose

10:57.491 --> 10:59.659
his mind when he sees you
in this bikini.

10:59.743 --> 11:02.537
No, I doubt it. I honestly think
he couldn't care less.

11:02.621 --> 11:04.915
- Come on, Belly.
- No, seriously.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.875
He didn't even get me
a present this year.

11:06.958 --> 11:08.210
- What?
- Yeah.

11:08.293 --> 11:09.294
He claimed he forgot.

11:09.378 --> 11:11.213
- Ugh, what a little bitch.
- Yeah.

11:11.296 --> 11:13.215
I can't believe you went against
my very sound advice

11:13.298 --> 11:14.841
and went and got
booed up anyway.

11:14.925 --> 11:16.968
I guess. [stammers]

11:17.052 --> 11:19.012
I mean, she's, like,
the hottest girl I've ever met.

11:19.096 --> 11:20.931
We know you're gossiping
about us over there.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.349
Yeah, you wish.

11:22.432 --> 11:24.309
[gasps] Let's play chicken.

11:24.393 --> 11:25.852
- No. Not chicken.
- Yes.

11:25.936 --> 11:27.062
I was like 12
the last time we played.

11:27.145 --> 11:28.855
Oh, come on, it'll be hilarious.

11:28.939 --> 11:30.690
Hey, I'm down. Come on, Steven.

11:30.774 --> 11:31.691
Fine.

11:31.775 --> 11:33.193
Dibs on Jeremy.

11:33.276 --> 11:35.695
Oh, great, that means
I'm stuck with Steven.

11:35.779 --> 11:36.738
That isn't fair.
Are you kidding me?

11:36.822 --> 11:37.781
Taylor's so much lighter.

11:37.864 --> 11:39.825
Oh, I'm sorry I'm so massive.

11:39.908 --> 11:42.285
- Wh...
- I wouldn't want to break
your delicate little shoulders.

11:42.369 --> 11:44.162
No, you're just taller
than her is all. That's...

11:44.246 --> 11:45.455
Oh, come on.

11:45.539 --> 11:46.998
You're such a complainer.
Let's just switch.

11:47.082 --> 11:48.542
Fine. Fine.

11:48.625 --> 11:50.127
- Let's take them down, Bell.
- [Steven] Fine. Ugh.

11:50.210 --> 11:51.962
- [giggling]
- You guys ready?

11:52.045 --> 11:53.130
- You're going down.
- [laughs]

11:53.213 --> 11:54.965
- Undefeated. Undefeated.
- Let's go. Let's go.

11:55.966 --> 11:58.051
[laughter]

11:58.135 --> 12:00.429
♪ ♪

12:00.512 --> 12:01.555
- Oh, my...
- Go.

12:01.638 --> 12:03.682
- No!
- Ugh, Steven.

12:03.765 --> 12:05.350
Why are your shoulders
so slippery?

12:05.434 --> 12:07.310
Uh, maybe it's all that oil
you slathered on your legs.

12:07.394 --> 12:09.438
Uh, maybe if you had
some hair on your chest,

12:09.521 --> 12:10.856
I wouldn't be sliding
all over the place.

12:10.939 --> 12:12.357
[Steven] Okay. Let's just go.
Let's just go.

12:12.441 --> 12:13.650
- [Jeremiah] Uh, go.
- [Steven] Come on, come on.

12:13.733 --> 12:16.695
All right. Three, two, one, go.

12:16.778 --> 12:18.321
- Hey!
- [laughter]

12:18.405 --> 12:20.699
- Hey, hold on.
- Oh, snap.

12:20.782 --> 12:22.117
- Oh, my God.
- [squealing]

12:22.200 --> 12:23.785
Come on.

12:25.203 --> 12:28.373
- Yeah! Whoo!
- Yeah! Give me some.

12:28.457 --> 12:30.542
- God, that was so your fault.
- That was completely
your fault.

12:30.625 --> 12:31.710
- What?
- Are you kidding me?

12:31.793 --> 12:32.878
- Still the champs.
- Yeah.

12:32.961 --> 12:34.337
- Still the champs.
- Hey, guys.

12:35.672 --> 12:36.673
Hey, Nicole.

12:36.756 --> 12:38.925
Hi. Happy birthday, Belly.

12:39.009 --> 12:41.636
Are you guys playing chicken?

12:41.720 --> 12:44.806
Um, yeah.
It was, it was Taylor's idea.

12:44.890 --> 12:46.308
Hey, I'm Taylor.

12:46.391 --> 12:47.851
- Hi.
- She's my best friend
from home.

12:47.934 --> 12:49.311
Just visiting for the weekend.

12:49.394 --> 12:50.353
Oh.

12:50.437 --> 12:52.856
- That's cute.
- Yeah.

12:55.233 --> 12:56.818
You guys want to play
a real game?

12:56.902 --> 12:58.278
- Yes.
- Yeah.
- Sounds good.

12:58.361 --> 13:01.239
[♪ Dayglow:
"Can I Call You Tonight?"]

13:02.782 --> 13:05.243
- Oh, oh.
- ♪ I feel close...

13:05.327 --> 13:07.704
- [groans]
- No!
- [cheers]

13:07.787 --> 13:09.122
[indistinct chatter]

13:09.206 --> 13:10.749
[Steven] Go, Jere.
I'm sorry, Jere.

13:10.832 --> 13:13.418
♪ It's a spotlight
stuck on the ceiling ♪

13:13.502 --> 13:15.212
♪ Why are these the things...

13:15.295 --> 13:16.671
- [others groan]
- You're slipping, Steven.

13:16.755 --> 13:18.298
- Yeah? Yeah?
- Yeah.

13:18.381 --> 13:20.550
- Okay. No, no, now it's on.
- [laughs]

13:20.634 --> 13:22.093
Got it.

13:22.177 --> 13:23.386
- Oh, yours, yours, yours.
- Oh, nice.

13:23.470 --> 13:25.305
Steven.

13:25.388 --> 13:26.598
Aw, we messed up.

13:26.681 --> 13:28.600
♪ Just how I feel...

13:29.935 --> 13:31.228
Got it.

13:31.311 --> 13:32.771
- [grunts]
- Oh!

13:32.854 --> 13:33.897
Oh!

13:33.980 --> 13:35.023
[imitates explosion]

13:35.106 --> 13:36.316
What you want, Belly? Belly.

13:36.399 --> 13:38.818
- Oh!
- Steven, it-it's you.

13:38.902 --> 13:41.321
- I don't think you're ready.
- Come on.

13:41.404 --> 13:43.406
- [music ends abruptly]
- [Nicole] Ow.

13:43.490 --> 13:44.491
[Taylor laughing] Oh, my God.

13:44.574 --> 13:45.825
- [Steven] Are you okay?
- I'm so sorry.

13:45.909 --> 13:47.369
- I didn't...
- [Belly] Taylor.

13:47.452 --> 13:48.954
It was an accident.

13:49.037 --> 13:50.580
I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

13:50.664 --> 13:52.415
Yeah, no,
I'm-I'm-I'm totally fine.

13:52.499 --> 13:53.583
Y-You guys keep playing.

13:53.667 --> 13:55.126
[Conrad] Let me see it.
Let's go inside.

13:55.210 --> 13:56.127
I'll get you some ice.

13:56.211 --> 13:57.546
[Nicole] Conrad, it's okay.

13:57.629 --> 13:59.506
[Belly] I'm so, so sorry
again, Nicole.

13:59.589 --> 14:00.966
- Feel better, okay?
- [Nicole] Yeah.

14:01.049 --> 14:03.260
- Yeah.
- Come on, Belly.

14:03.343 --> 14:05.220
Conrad can take care of Nicole.

14:05.303 --> 14:06.555
Let's go inside
and look at ourselves

14:06.638 --> 14:07.847
in the mirror some more.

14:12.018 --> 14:14.437
Yeah, have fun with that.

14:16.815 --> 14:18.275
[door opens]

14:19.484 --> 14:20.610
[Conrad] Does it hurt?

14:20.694 --> 14:22.445
Conrad, I told you I was fine.

14:22.529 --> 14:25.365
I know. I just...

14:25.448 --> 14:26.616
- care.
- [laughs]

14:26.700 --> 14:28.326
Well, thank you
for taking care of me.

14:28.410 --> 14:29.953
Any time.

14:32.289 --> 14:33.206
[cell phone chimes]

14:33.290 --> 14:34.624
Sorry.

14:34.708 --> 14:36.126
[sighs]

14:37.752 --> 14:39.212
Oh, fuck.

14:40.171 --> 14:42.674
Oh, God. Um, I'm sorry,
I got to, I got to go.

14:42.757 --> 14:44.259
- Uh... Okay.
- I'm late.

14:44.342 --> 14:45.885
- Bye.
- [door opens]

14:45.969 --> 14:48.096
[door closes]

14:48.179 --> 14:49.472
[sighs]

14:51.141 --> 14:52.601
[sighs]

14:52.684 --> 14:54.894
- That's cute.
- Mm-hmm.

14:54.978 --> 14:56.938
What's happening
at the bookstore?

14:57.022 --> 14:59.149
I don't know.
Should we rubberneck?

14:59.232 --> 15:00.775
- Always.
- [laughs] Excuse me.

15:00.859 --> 15:03.737
Excuse me. Oh.

15:06.072 --> 15:09.743
Am I crazy, or does
Cleveland Castillo look... good?

15:11.995 --> 15:13.413
No, it's the celibacy talking.

15:13.496 --> 15:17.083
I think he might just be perfect
"sex after divorce" material.

15:17.167 --> 15:18.752
- What?
- What? Didn't you say
you devoured his book

15:18.835 --> 15:20.253
- in like a day?
- Yeah, but then

15:20.337 --> 15:22.464
I read that essay
in The New Yorker about his ex.

15:22.547 --> 15:23.840
He's gay.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.967
I read that essay, too.
He is not gay.

15:26.051 --> 15:27.844
He's bi.

15:27.927 --> 15:30.055
What? Does that
make a difference?

15:30.138 --> 15:32.390
- Of course not.
- Well... then what's the harm

15:32.474 --> 15:34.684
in a little summer fling?

15:34.768 --> 15:36.770
I'd rather be here with you.

15:36.853 --> 15:39.397
Darling, you already are.

15:39.481 --> 15:40.982
Live a little.

15:41.066 --> 15:42.317
[Conrad] Excuse me. Excuse me.

15:42.400 --> 15:44.444
- [both] Connie.
- Hey, sorry, I'm late.

15:44.527 --> 15:47.322
Yeah, I would love
to talk about the book

15:47.405 --> 15:49.032
that, uh, I'm about to write.

15:49.115 --> 15:51.159
- It's, uh, it's about sailing.
- [sighs]

15:51.242 --> 15:53.620
♪ ♪

15:58.875 --> 16:01.127
I don't know what to think
about you this summer.

16:02.212 --> 16:03.963
What do you mean?

16:05.131 --> 16:07.592
Suddenly,
you care about clothes.

16:07.676 --> 16:10.011
You have new friends.
You have a boyfriend.

16:10.095 --> 16:12.305
Yeah, well, I told you
this summer would be different.

16:12.389 --> 16:14.432
I know. I have to admit...

16:14.516 --> 16:17.560
I'm kind of freaked out
by your glow-up.

16:17.644 --> 16:18.937
Oh, don't you always say,

16:19.020 --> 16:21.022
"Belly, don't be
so afraid of change"?

16:21.106 --> 16:23.024
No, I know, I know.

16:23.108 --> 16:25.068
Can you just promise me
one thing?

16:25.151 --> 16:28.279
- Yeah, anything.
- We'll always be best friends?

16:28.363 --> 16:30.699
That'll never change.

16:30.782 --> 16:32.450
Best friends forever.

16:32.534 --> 16:33.743
[laughing] Come on.

16:35.245 --> 16:37.372
[gull screeching]

16:39.915 --> 16:41.960
I thought we were
keeping dinner simple.

16:42.043 --> 16:44.587
It's Belly's sweet 16.

16:44.671 --> 16:46.506
Is Connie done
shucking the corn?

16:46.589 --> 16:48.883
[Laurel] Mm, not yet.

16:48.967 --> 16:50.719
I can't believe he forgot
Belly's birthday.

16:50.802 --> 16:52.387
What's up with that?

16:52.470 --> 16:54.013
He's been shut down like this
since April.

16:54.097 --> 16:55.598
When he and his girlfriend
broke up?

16:55.682 --> 16:58.560
Yeah, but he won't
talk to me about it.

16:58.643 --> 17:00.437
I just, I want
to make sure he's okay.

17:00.520 --> 17:02.689
Remember that time he broke
his arm and didn't tell anyone

17:02.772 --> 17:04.648
because he didn't want
to be a bother?

17:04.733 --> 17:06.943
Classic Connie.

17:09.820 --> 17:11.489
Do you think maybe
you could talk to him?

17:11.573 --> 17:13.575
I mean, you-you've always had
a way of making him open up.

17:15.410 --> 17:16.618
I'm on it.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.915
[door opens]

17:23.542 --> 17:24.961
[door closes]

17:27.964 --> 17:29.632
'Sup, Laurel?

17:29.716 --> 17:32.177
I just wanted
to check in with you.

17:32.260 --> 17:33.303
Okay.

17:33.386 --> 17:35.096
How have you been?

17:35.180 --> 17:36.556
Fine.

17:36.639 --> 17:37.849
[mocking] "Fine."

17:37.932 --> 17:39.684
We used to talk.

17:39.768 --> 17:41.853
- We still talk.
- Barely.

17:43.313 --> 17:45.982
You're still my special guy,
you know.

17:46.065 --> 17:48.735
You're the first baby.

17:48.818 --> 17:51.404
You can talk to me
about anything.

17:51.488 --> 17:52.572
Thank you.

17:52.655 --> 17:54.657
♪ ♪

17:57.285 --> 17:59.370
You know...

17:59.454 --> 18:01.498
you don't have to hold
everything in all the time.

18:05.376 --> 18:07.796
You don't always
have to be strong.

18:16.346 --> 18:18.431
I know.

18:18.515 --> 18:20.183
I'm just...

18:20.266 --> 18:22.060
It's been a while
since I was your age,

18:22.143 --> 18:25.688
but I still remember what it was
like to have my heart broken.

18:25.772 --> 18:29.442
Losing your first love,
it hurts,

18:29.526 --> 18:31.903
and it takes time
to get over it.

18:35.240 --> 18:36.908
Aubrey, yeah.

18:36.991 --> 18:40.411
Yeah, yeah, no. That was brutal.

18:40.495 --> 18:42.038
Yeah.

18:45.291 --> 18:47.836
- [laughter]
- [indistinct conversation]

18:47.919 --> 18:49.796
♪ ♪

18:54.050 --> 18:56.094
Wow. Cool.

18:58.721 --> 19:00.598
- [Cam] This is delicious.
- [Belly] Yeah.

19:00.682 --> 19:02.267
- [Susannah] Of course it is.
- So, Cam.

19:02.350 --> 19:04.769
You mind if I call you
Cam Cameron?

19:04.853 --> 19:06.813
Mm-hmm. Yeah, man.
Feel free. That's funny.

19:06.896 --> 19:08.606
- Cool.
- [Susannah] I'm glad
you're here, Cameron.

19:08.690 --> 19:10.608
I know your mom,
Denise, from the club.

19:10.692 --> 19:12.026
I have heard a lot about you.

19:12.110 --> 19:13.444
Thank you so much
for having me, Susannah.

19:13.528 --> 19:14.445
My mom says hi.

19:14.529 --> 19:15.864
- Mm.
- [Laurel] Cam, have you

19:15.947 --> 19:17.031
ever had miyeok-guk before?

19:17.115 --> 19:18.491
It's a Korean
birthday tradition.

19:18.575 --> 19:20.827
No. Looks so good. Thank you.

19:20.910 --> 19:23.037
Belly told me you're vegetarian,
so I didn't put any meat in it.

19:23.121 --> 19:24.956
Thank you, Laurel. Oh, geez.

19:25.039 --> 19:26.833
Why don't you eat meat,
Cam Cameron?

19:26.916 --> 19:28.668
Uh, the meat industry
is, like, the number one

19:28.751 --> 19:30.378
- contributor to global warming.
- Mm.

19:30.461 --> 19:32.755
And I just, I like animals.

19:32.839 --> 19:35.550
Just don't come for my
leather jacket. [chuckles]

19:35.633 --> 19:37.969
- I'm pretty sure
you mean pleather.
- [Jeremiah] Ooh.

19:38.052 --> 19:39.721
[laughs]

19:39.804 --> 19:41.598
You know, uh, actually,
Belly eats meat.

19:41.681 --> 19:43.558
So, you let her kiss you
with those lips?

19:43.641 --> 19:44.559
Guys.

19:44.642 --> 19:46.769
- [laughter]
- Stop.

19:46.853 --> 19:48.771
No, I don't judge people
for eating meat.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.690
It's just, like,
a personal choice. I don't care.

19:50.773 --> 19:52.859
So you don't mind if, uh,
like, her lips touch

19:52.942 --> 19:54.861
a dead animal, and then
those dead animal lips

19:54.944 --> 19:56.779
- touch your lips, right? Ow.
- [kick]

19:56.863 --> 19:58.740
[chuckles] I don't mind at all.

19:58.823 --> 20:01.451
Um, in fact...

20:04.245 --> 20:05.413
[sighs] Aw.

20:05.496 --> 20:07.123
[both pretend to retch]

20:07.206 --> 20:08.791
[Laurel] All right.

20:08.875 --> 20:10.585
All right, all right.

20:10.668 --> 20:12.170
Belly's allowed to kiss,

20:12.253 --> 20:14.255
but that's it. [laughs]

20:14.339 --> 20:16.883
Mom, please. No.
You're so not funny.

20:16.966 --> 20:19.135
- No more wine for you, okay?
- [Steven] I'm sorry. I just

20:19.218 --> 20:21.888
don't understand why anybody
would want to kiss somebody

20:21.971 --> 20:24.974
who once fully shat
in the bathtub.

20:25.058 --> 20:26.351
I was like two years old.

20:26.434 --> 20:27.977
- Two? More like six.
- Six.

20:28.061 --> 20:29.729
- Shut up, Steven.
- Steven.

20:29.812 --> 20:31.439
Aw, I remember that.

20:31.522 --> 20:33.358
God, that feels like
a lifetime ago.

20:33.441 --> 20:35.151
I remember when I visited
last summer,

20:35.234 --> 20:37.737
and you and you dared him

20:37.820 --> 20:40.073
to pee in the fireplace,
and you stunk up

20:40.156 --> 20:42.617
the entire house for days.
Do you remember that?

20:42.700 --> 20:46.120
[laughter, groaning]

20:47.664 --> 20:49.916
I blamed the neighbor's cat.

20:49.999 --> 20:52.085
We were drunk. We were drunk.

20:52.168 --> 20:55.296
- On like half a White Claw.
- [laughter]

20:55.380 --> 20:57.048
She got you there.

20:59.467 --> 21:01.052
You know, um, I'm thinking

21:01.135 --> 21:02.470
maybe we should go
to Nicole's party.

21:02.553 --> 21:04.347
Yes.

21:04.430 --> 21:06.724
Oh, my God. I love you.
I'm so excited.

21:08.643 --> 21:10.895
- Ow. Oh...
- It goes on your lashes,

21:10.979 --> 21:13.773
- not in your eyeball.
- Uh, yeah, that's what
I'm trying to do.

21:13.856 --> 21:16.317
- Just let me do it.
- [sighs]

21:16.401 --> 21:17.986
Tonight is gonna be so much fun.

21:18.069 --> 21:19.654
Yeah, I just hope
it's not a disaster

21:19.737 --> 21:21.072
like the last party I went to.

21:21.155 --> 21:22.907
You went to one party
for like 20 minutes.

21:22.991 --> 21:24.325
It barely even counts.

21:24.409 --> 21:26.411
Yeah, and I embarrassed myself
in front of everyone.

21:26.494 --> 21:28.329
No, you made people notice you.

21:28.413 --> 21:30.873
Enjoy it. Don't spoil it.

21:30.957 --> 21:32.750
I mean, I guess
it was pretty badass

21:32.834 --> 21:35.169
having a black eye for a day.

21:35.253 --> 21:36.462
Zero clumps.

21:36.546 --> 21:38.089
I'm a genius.

21:38.172 --> 21:41.634
Oh, we should totally
wear these to the party.

21:41.718 --> 21:44.303
Wh... I mean, Susannah got those
as, like, a fun thing

21:44.387 --> 21:46.848
for my birthday dinner.
Isn't it weird if we wear them

21:46.931 --> 21:48.224
- out of the house?
- No.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.101
It's hot.

21:52.270 --> 21:54.272
Look at us.

21:54.355 --> 21:56.941
We're hot-ass bitches.

21:57.025 --> 21:58.943
[♪ Saweetie: "Best Friend"]

21:59.027 --> 22:01.029
[indistinct conversation]

22:10.121 --> 22:13.374
♪ That my best friend,
she a real bad ♪

22:13.458 --> 22:15.877
♪ Got her own money,
she don't need no ♪

22:15.960 --> 22:18.546
♪ On the dance floor,
she had two, three drinks ♪

22:18.629 --> 22:21.007
♪ Now she twerking, she throw
it out and come back in...

22:21.090 --> 22:22.759
[Jeremiah] You know
I've dated your daughter.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.761
- Um...
- [laughter]

22:25.803 --> 22:28.264
- Whoo!
- [cheers]

22:28.347 --> 22:31.559
Dude. That was awesome.

22:31.642 --> 22:34.187
♪ Beep, beep, is that
my bestie in a Tessie...

22:34.270 --> 22:36.689
Belly, you came!

22:36.773 --> 22:38.566
Hey, Nicole. You look so pretty.

22:38.649 --> 22:41.736
Oh, me? Look at you.
Oh, my goodness.

22:41.819 --> 22:43.863
- Are those real flowers?
- Yes.

22:43.946 --> 22:45.823
[Nicole] Incredible.
Well, we have to show Gigi.

22:45.907 --> 22:47.116
Yeah, yeah, totally.

22:47.200 --> 22:49.368
- You want to come?
- You have fun over there.

22:49.452 --> 22:51.621
- Okay. Okay.
- I'm gonna go find a drink.

22:51.704 --> 22:53.790
You guys, look who's here.

22:53.873 --> 22:55.208
[girl] Birthday girl.

22:55.291 --> 22:57.960
- Happy birthday.
- Happy birthday.

22:59.087 --> 23:00.713
Thank you. Thank you, guys.

23:00.797 --> 23:02.423
Um, is this for me?

23:02.507 --> 23:04.217
Who else would it be for, Belly?

23:04.300 --> 23:06.260
Oh, my... Thank you, guys.

23:06.344 --> 23:07.887
- [laughter]
- Yeah.

23:07.970 --> 23:10.264
These cakes are amazing, Nicole.

23:10.348 --> 23:12.892
I never miss a chance to have
a Sofia Coppola moment.

23:12.975 --> 23:15.770
- [laughter]
- Okay, well,
Belly, make a wish.

23:15.853 --> 23:17.271
Okay.

23:20.358 --> 23:23.027
[cheers, laughter]

23:23.111 --> 23:24.362
Oh, Belly, where's Jeremiah?

23:24.445 --> 23:26.697
Um, I think he's over
by the drinks table.

23:26.781 --> 23:28.825
Who's thirsty?

23:28.908 --> 23:31.494
- You, clearly.
- [laughter]

23:31.577 --> 23:33.454
[Jeremiah] Yeah? Well,
I'll give you some lessons.

23:33.538 --> 23:34.664
I'm really good, actually.

23:34.747 --> 23:37.750
- I'll hold you to that.
- Hey, all about it.

23:37.834 --> 23:39.836
So, how come I've never
seen you at the pool?

23:39.919 --> 23:42.547
My parents had one put in, so...

23:42.630 --> 23:45.466
Hmm. Does your parents' pool
have all this?

23:45.550 --> 23:46.968
Queerbaiter.

23:47.051 --> 23:50.680
[chuckles] No, Luke,
I'm just equal opportunity.

23:54.350 --> 23:57.645
So, Nicole, you and Conrad
a thing or what?

23:57.728 --> 24:00.731
I think "or what."

24:00.815 --> 24:03.651
Wait, you live with him.
You should know what he's up to.

24:03.734 --> 24:05.820
Has he been hanging out
with other girls this summer?

24:07.363 --> 24:09.866
No, he-he's always off
by himself.

24:09.949 --> 24:12.493
Okay, well, new topic.

24:12.577 --> 24:14.495
Have you asked Cam
to the ball yet?

24:14.579 --> 24:16.956
No, I was gonna, uh,
do it before dinner today,

24:17.039 --> 24:18.916
but, um, everyone was there.

24:19.000 --> 24:20.918
Do it right now.
Just-just ask him.

24:21.002 --> 24:22.461
What you're gonna do is
you're gonna take him

24:22.545 --> 24:24.130
to an empty bedroom
and ask him there.

24:24.213 --> 24:26.507
No. Do not do that.
He'll get too excited.

24:26.591 --> 24:28.342
- That's the point.
He'll say yes.
- Gigi.

24:28.426 --> 24:30.303
- [Gigi] That was my plan.
- [Nicole] I know.

24:30.386 --> 24:32.430
That's bad advice.

24:32.513 --> 24:35.099
[conversation fades]

24:35.183 --> 24:37.185
♪ ♪

24:44.984 --> 24:46.485
[Gigi] No,
it's a great plan, guys.

24:46.569 --> 24:48.070
That was my plan for tonight.

24:48.154 --> 24:50.573
- I know.
That is a terrible plan.
- [laughing]

24:50.656 --> 24:53.117
♪ Hold up, get this ♪

24:53.201 --> 24:55.828
♪ Let me break it down to you
for a quick fix ♪

24:55.912 --> 24:57.413
♪ This a piece of cake,
finna have a picnic ♪

24:57.496 --> 24:58.414
♪ Ooh, child's play...

24:58.497 --> 25:00.791
That looks fancy.

25:00.875 --> 25:02.543
Personally,
I'd rather be comfortable.

25:02.627 --> 25:06.005
Yeah. Uh, well, fancy
isn't always better, so...

25:06.088 --> 25:09.217
I don't think Belly agrees.

25:09.300 --> 25:13.262
She seems fully on board
with the fancy girls.

25:13.346 --> 25:15.431
No, no, no, no. Look,
she's just trying it out.

25:15.514 --> 25:18.726
Look, girls like that, they're
cool in theory, all right,

25:18.809 --> 25:21.020
but Belly's never gonna feel
fully comfortable around them.

25:21.103 --> 25:23.856
- [scoffs]
- Come on, look,
she's always gonna need you.

25:23.940 --> 25:25.483
All right?
You're, like, her number one.

25:25.566 --> 25:27.443
Come on.

25:27.526 --> 25:29.654
Okay.

25:29.737 --> 25:32.031
This line hasn't budged.
Do you want to go upstairs

25:32.114 --> 25:33.658
and see if there are
other bathrooms?

25:33.741 --> 25:35.409
Yeah, sure.

25:35.493 --> 25:37.078
♪ Ain't nothing to this...

25:37.161 --> 25:38.829
[Jeremiah] So, what are you guys
doing after the party?

25:38.913 --> 25:40.873
- I have plans, but I think...
- Oh, you're busy?

25:40.957 --> 25:42.708
- ...he's free, right?
- That's a shame.

25:42.792 --> 25:44.168
[laughs]

25:46.170 --> 25:47.964
Yeah, I'll be right back.

25:51.550 --> 25:53.094
[feedback squeals]

25:53.177 --> 25:54.387
Testing, testing,
one, two, three.

25:54.470 --> 25:55.805
Checking out, checking out.

25:55.888 --> 25:57.014
All right.

25:57.098 --> 25:58.808
This one goes out to Cam Cameron

25:58.891 --> 26:01.310
and our favorite little
Belly Button.

26:01.394 --> 26:02.853
[♪ "Summer Nights" from Grease]

26:02.937 --> 26:04.855
- [laughs]
- Oh, Jesus.

26:04.939 --> 26:06.941
[cheering]

26:10.236 --> 26:13.614
♪ Summer loving,
had me a blast ♪

26:13.698 --> 26:15.283
No, please no.

26:15.366 --> 26:17.410
Oh, come on.

26:17.493 --> 26:21.622
♪ I met a girl crazy for me ♪

26:21.706 --> 26:24.625
♪ I met a boy
as cute as can be ♪

26:24.709 --> 26:28.754
♪ Summer days drifting away ♪

26:28.838 --> 26:31.465
♪ To, oh, oh,
the summer nights ♪

26:31.549 --> 26:33.301
♪ Oh, well-a, well-a, well-a ♪

26:33.384 --> 26:35.553
♪ Tell me more, tell me more ♪

26:35.636 --> 26:37.263
♪ Did you get very far? ♪

26:37.346 --> 26:39.265
♪ Tell me more, tell me more ♪

26:39.348 --> 26:41.058
♪ Like, does he have a car? ♪

26:41.142 --> 26:43.019
♪ Uh-huh, do, do,
uh-huh, do, do ♪

26:43.102 --> 26:44.562
♪ Uh-huh, do, do, do, do, do ♪

26:44.645 --> 26:46.814
♪ Uh-huh, do, do,
uh-huh, do, do ♪

26:46.897 --> 26:48.774
♪ Uh-huh, do, do, do, do, do ♪

26:48.858 --> 26:52.486
♪ She swam by me,
she got a cramp ♪

26:52.570 --> 26:55.823
- Taylor?
- ♪ He ran by me,
got my suit damp ♪

26:55.906 --> 26:58.909
♪ I saved her life,
she nearly drowned...

26:58.993 --> 27:01.037
- [♪ Billie Eilish:
"Happier Than Ever"]
- ♪ Driving home ♪

27:01.120 --> 27:03.748
♪ Under the influence ♪

27:03.831 --> 27:05.750
♪ You scared me to death...

27:05.833 --> 27:07.460
Taylor? Are you in here?

27:07.543 --> 27:09.211
[boy coughing] Yo,
close that door!

27:09.295 --> 27:11.839
[Belly chuckles] Sorry, sorry.

27:11.922 --> 27:14.842
♪ I don't relate to you...

27:16.844 --> 27:19.388
Taylor?

27:19.472 --> 27:22.933
♪ 'Cause I'd never
treat me this shitty ♪

27:24.310 --> 27:28.064
♪ You made me hate this city ♪

27:28.147 --> 27:30.733
♪ And I don't talk shit
about you...

27:30.816 --> 27:32.651
- Oh, my God.
- Hmm?

27:32.735 --> 27:34.028
- Belly?
- Oh, my God. Uh...

27:34.111 --> 27:36.238
- Jesus.
- Steven...
- [Belly] Oh, my...

27:36.322 --> 27:37.615
You're hooking up
with my brother?

27:37.698 --> 27:38.741
I swear it just happened.

27:38.824 --> 27:40.326
Well, what, you got bored?

27:40.409 --> 27:41.744
H-He's dating someone, you know.

27:41.827 --> 27:43.162
Someone he actually likes.

27:43.245 --> 27:45.039
You saying he couldn't like
someone like me?

27:45.122 --> 27:46.624
No. No, no, no.
That's not what I'm saying.

27:46.707 --> 27:47.917
I... [exhales]

27:48.000 --> 27:49.335
This could get really messed up.

27:49.418 --> 27:51.045
I mean, he's taking her
to the deb ball.

27:51.128 --> 27:52.671
And all those girls
are her friends.

27:52.755 --> 27:54.590
Oh, my God, I'm so sick

27:54.673 --> 27:57.218
of hearing about
this fucking deb ball.

27:57.301 --> 27:58.886
I don't even know
who you are anymore.

27:58.969 --> 28:00.638
Oh, why?
Because I'm not just going along

28:00.721 --> 28:02.056
with everything you want to do?

28:02.139 --> 28:03.516
Is that why you threw yourself
at my brother?

28:03.599 --> 28:05.017
So that you could
get back at me?

28:05.101 --> 28:08.521
You know, you act
so innocent, Belly,

28:08.604 --> 28:09.730
like you're the victim.

28:09.814 --> 28:11.732
- Victim? How do I... I'm sorry.
- Yeah, but...

28:11.816 --> 28:14.402
I think you're
the self-absorbed one, Belly.

28:14.485 --> 28:17.279
How do you not know that I've
had a crush on Steven for years?

28:17.363 --> 28:18.739
If you weren't
so obsessed with Conrad...

28:18.823 --> 28:20.866
[shushes] What is wrong
with you?

28:20.950 --> 28:22.952
People are going to hear.

28:23.035 --> 28:25.162
Who cares? There's more
than one story happening here,

28:25.246 --> 28:26.997
but you seem to only care
about the one

28:27.081 --> 28:28.624
where you're the main character.

28:30.543 --> 28:33.254
I... I can't deal
with this right now.

28:33.337 --> 28:34.964
I got to go.

28:36.257 --> 28:41.178
♪ Just fuckin' leave me alone...

28:41.262 --> 28:43.139
You're not gonna make it.
You got nothing.

28:43.222 --> 28:44.557
- So much shit you talk...
- Try.

28:44.640 --> 28:46.851
- Oh.
- [imitates buzzer]

28:47.893 --> 28:49.437
Really? Not even close.

28:49.520 --> 28:51.939
Wait, Cam, have you started
the waltz lessons yet?

28:52.022 --> 28:53.649
Ms. Covington's a real sadist.

28:53.732 --> 28:55.151
Who you talking about?

28:55.234 --> 28:57.862
The-the dance teacher.
For the ball.

28:57.945 --> 28:59.238
- Oh.
- Yeah.

28:59.321 --> 29:00.656
Belly hasn't
really asked me yet.

29:00.739 --> 29:02.992
[Jeremiah] Oh, dude,
I'm sure she will.

29:03.075 --> 29:04.785
- Trust me.
- Yeah.

29:04.869 --> 29:06.495
- Seriously.
- If you say so.

29:07.621 --> 29:08.664
- Oh!
- Psych.

29:08.747 --> 29:09.915
Oh, that was close.

29:09.999 --> 29:11.000
All right, that was close.
Ready?

29:11.083 --> 29:12.084
All right, ready?

29:12.168 --> 29:13.627
Go ahead, man.

29:13.711 --> 29:15.004
- Don't mess up.
- Hey.

29:15.087 --> 29:17.214
- Hi.
- [gasps] Belly.

29:17.298 --> 29:18.632
[Jeremiah laughs] Hi.

29:18.716 --> 29:20.634
Where have you been?

29:20.718 --> 29:23.262
Yeah. Um, I-I thought
you didn't drink.

29:23.345 --> 29:24.472
Oh, it's water. It's water.

29:24.555 --> 29:25.848
Jeremiah's been drinking for me.

29:25.931 --> 29:27.683
Mm-hmm. I love this kid so much.

29:27.766 --> 29:30.769
- So fun.
- Um, hey, can we leave?
Like, now?

29:30.853 --> 29:32.771
Yeah, um, yeah.
Sure, that's cool.

29:32.855 --> 29:34.940
- Oh.
- Uh, I'll see you later.

29:35.024 --> 29:37.026
- [Jeremiah] Yeah, have fun.
- Good luck, good luck.

29:37.109 --> 29:38.819
Two v. one, all right?

29:38.903 --> 29:40.196
You guys are going down. Ready?

29:40.279 --> 29:41.906
- Yeah, right.
- Oh!

29:41.989 --> 29:44.116
- [whoops]
- Nice shot.

29:44.200 --> 29:46.827
[Jeremiah] You owe me
five bucks. I told you...

29:46.911 --> 29:48.829
So, can I ask you something?

29:48.913 --> 29:50.372
Yeah.

29:50.456 --> 29:52.249
Are you, um...

29:52.333 --> 29:54.793
Are you into Jeremiah?

29:54.877 --> 29:56.629
You mean Conrad?

29:56.712 --> 29:57.838
What? Con...

29:57.922 --> 30:00.216
No. No, no. J-Jeremiah.

30:00.299 --> 30:01.926
I just kind of got
a vibe from you guys.

30:02.009 --> 30:03.802
No, no, no.
That's, that's just Jere.

30:03.886 --> 30:05.721
He flirts with everyone.

30:05.804 --> 30:07.765
Susannah likes to joke that
he's like a-a golden retriever.

30:07.848 --> 30:09.725
[laughs]

30:09.808 --> 30:12.102
Personally, I think he exudes
a little more border collie.

30:12.186 --> 30:14.188
Yeah, I can see that, too. Yeah.

30:15.606 --> 30:18.108
Um, thanks for coming tonight.

30:18.192 --> 30:20.736
No problem, Flavia.

30:21.904 --> 30:23.280
Hey, I-I... [sighs]

30:23.364 --> 30:24.698
I've been meaning
to ask you something.

30:24.782 --> 30:26.408
Yeah?

30:26.492 --> 30:28.911
Yeah, um...

30:33.874 --> 30:37.670
Does it ever feel weird being
the only one who's not drinking?

30:38.879 --> 30:41.173
Uh, no. No, it's... cool.

30:41.257 --> 30:43.217
[laughs] Cool.

30:44.260 --> 30:45.803
Is that it?

30:45.886 --> 30:48.347
Yeah. That's it.

30:48.430 --> 30:50.057
Okay.

30:53.143 --> 30:54.812
Thanks.

30:54.895 --> 30:56.897
♪ ♪

31:11.787 --> 31:13.622
[sniffs]

31:16.166 --> 31:17.501
[footsteps approaching]

31:17.585 --> 31:21.380
- Morning.
- Good morning, Bells.

31:21.463 --> 31:23.132
Mmm. Want one?

31:26.552 --> 31:27.886
[laughs softly] Okay.

31:27.970 --> 31:29.471
I take it you and Tay-Tay
haven't made up yet?

31:29.555 --> 31:31.056
Nope.

31:31.140 --> 31:32.891
We haven't talked
since last night.

31:32.975 --> 31:35.269
Mm. Here.

31:36.729 --> 31:38.105
Thanks.

31:39.148 --> 31:40.190
Well, when does she leave?

31:40.274 --> 31:41.317
Uh, in a couple hours.

31:41.400 --> 31:43.527
- She's upstairs packing now.
- Mm.

31:43.611 --> 31:45.321
Hey, do you want
to go on a muffin run?

31:45.404 --> 31:47.156
I-I have to get
out of the house.

31:47.239 --> 31:49.241
I'm always down
for a muffin run.

31:49.325 --> 31:50.826
Uh, I'm gonna make a to-go cup.

31:50.909 --> 31:53.454
Do you mind grabbing the keys
from Conrad's room?

31:53.537 --> 31:55.581
Yeah, sure. Uh, is he home?

31:55.664 --> 31:56.915
No, he spent the night
at Nicole's.

31:56.999 --> 31:59.293
Oh. Um...

31:59.376 --> 32:00.836
Do you know where
he keeps the keys?

32:00.919 --> 32:03.505
Uh, th-they should be
in his desk.

32:06.175 --> 32:08.177
♪ ♪

32:31.450 --> 32:32.785
[groans]

32:49.968 --> 32:52.262
[Belly] At least
he remembered infinity.

32:57.267 --> 32:59.269
Doesn't he know, for him,

32:59.353 --> 33:02.272
I would've traveled endlessly
around those curves?

33:02.356 --> 33:04.942
[♪ Carly Rae Jepsen:
"Your Type"]

33:05.025 --> 33:07.152
♪ I used to be in love
with you ♪

33:09.446 --> 33:13.242
♪ You used to be
the first thing on my mind ♪

33:14.868 --> 33:17.538
♪ I know I'm just
a friend to you ♪

33:20.165 --> 33:24.253
♪ That I will never get
to call you mine...

33:24.336 --> 33:25.921
You good?

33:26.004 --> 33:27.423
♪ I'm sorry, I'm sorry...

33:27.506 --> 33:30.467
I just, I don't get Conrad
this summer.

33:30.551 --> 33:33.929
Why? Is it because
he forgot your birthday?

33:34.012 --> 33:36.473
No. It's because
he's been acting weird

33:36.557 --> 33:38.392
since the first day
that I got here.

33:38.475 --> 33:40.978
Yeah, trust me,
he's been weird for months.

33:41.061 --> 33:43.063
Just forget him.

33:43.147 --> 33:44.773
♪ To the spot that we met...

33:44.857 --> 33:47.192
Look, I-I'm happy
you invited Cam last night.

33:47.276 --> 33:48.694
He's really cool.

33:48.777 --> 33:51.155
Have you asked him
to the deb ball yet?

33:51.238 --> 33:52.406
No.

33:52.489 --> 33:54.324
♪ You call more than a friend...

33:54.408 --> 33:56.744
Look, I-I know Steven and I were
giving him some shit,

33:56.827 --> 33:58.370
- but...
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

33:58.454 --> 33:59.955
[chuckles]

34:00.038 --> 34:02.291
But I think he's really cool.

34:02.374 --> 34:04.626
- And I think you should...
- Nicole really likes Conrad.

34:04.710 --> 34:08.755
And if he's not into her,
that's just messed up.

34:08.839 --> 34:11.632
- [Jeremiah sighs]
- What?

34:11.717 --> 34:13.217
[laughs] Nothing.

34:13.302 --> 34:15.763
It's just, last night,
you were all about Cam Cameron,

34:15.846 --> 34:19.516
and-and today you can't stop
obsessing over Conrad.

34:19.600 --> 34:22.268
[scoffs]
Why are you so grumpy, huh?

34:22.351 --> 34:24.103
Did things not go well
with Luke last night?

34:24.188 --> 34:26.148
- [both chuckle]
- Stop.

34:26.231 --> 34:28.317
Actually,
things went really well.

34:28.400 --> 34:29.860
Want to hear details?

34:29.943 --> 34:32.112
- You sure?
- Oh, shut up.

34:32.196 --> 34:34.197
[both laugh]

34:34.281 --> 34:37.242
♪ I'll make time for you ♪

34:37.326 --> 34:39.786
♪ Time for you, ooh ♪

34:39.870 --> 34:41.830
♪ I'll make time for you ♪

34:41.914 --> 34:45.542
♪ Time for you, ooh ♪♪

34:47.920 --> 34:49.129
You're early.

34:51.547 --> 34:54.717
So, what knot are you gonna
torture me with today, hmm?

34:55.761 --> 34:58.013
You gonna tell me I fucked up?

34:58.096 --> 34:59.848
That's more the role
of a parent,

34:59.932 --> 35:01.558
and, uh...

35:01.642 --> 35:03.602
you know,
I'm not one for a reason.

35:05.354 --> 35:07.898
So I'm not, like, fired?

35:07.981 --> 35:10.400
[laughs softly]

35:10.484 --> 35:12.820
Look, you were supposed
to help me prep.

35:12.903 --> 35:15.113
Is it the end of the world

35:15.197 --> 35:18.033
that you showed up late
and I made up some shit

35:18.116 --> 35:19.910
about sailing
on national television?

35:19.993 --> 35:21.495
Not really.

35:23.205 --> 35:26.542
Well, thanks
for not being pissed.

35:30.003 --> 35:31.296
So, be real with me.

35:32.381 --> 35:33.423
Why were you late?

35:33.507 --> 35:35.425
Um...

35:35.509 --> 35:37.511
I was with a girl.
We lost track of time.

35:37.594 --> 35:39.972
[sighs] Oh, man, to be 17 again.

35:40.055 --> 35:41.807
No, it wasn't like that.

35:41.890 --> 35:43.684
Sure, if you say so.

35:43.767 --> 35:46.061
Well, good for you, man.

35:46.144 --> 35:49.606
Just be on time
from now on. Cool?

35:50.649 --> 35:51.942
Cool.

35:54.444 --> 35:55.988
You've been practicing
your bowline?

35:56.071 --> 35:57.656
- Hours...
- Yeah?

35:57.739 --> 36:00.534
...and hours of practice,

36:00.617 --> 36:03.662
so that I can do that.

36:04.913 --> 36:07.082
That's what I call a bowline.
It's a nice one, too.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.709
[Cleveland] I think I'm ready
for the America's Cup.

36:09.751 --> 36:11.753
♪ ♪

36:18.051 --> 36:20.137
You're not going to say goodbye?

36:20.220 --> 36:21.430
I don't feel like it.

36:22.764 --> 36:24.349
She's your best friend.

36:24.433 --> 36:26.518
And she came out here
on your birthday

36:26.602 --> 36:28.270
because she loves you.

36:28.353 --> 36:30.272
♪ ♪

36:30.355 --> 36:32.190
Fine.

36:33.358 --> 36:35.777
[woman] Call me
when you get there.

36:35.861 --> 36:37.070
[Belly] Hey.

36:38.071 --> 36:39.573
Hey.

36:42.326 --> 36:43.911
Have a safe trip.

36:43.994 --> 36:45.203
Thanks.

36:47.122 --> 36:49.875
- Okay.
- Uh, and about last night,

36:49.958 --> 36:52.502
you'll be happy to know
that it'll never happen again.

36:52.586 --> 36:53.962
Steven said
that it was a mistake

36:54.046 --> 36:56.173
and we never should have
gone there, so...

36:56.256 --> 36:58.800
you know, it's whatever.

37:05.807 --> 37:07.935
Look, I'm not mad. I...

37:08.018 --> 37:09.811
I'm just kind of weirded out.

37:09.895 --> 37:11.521
Um...

37:12.648 --> 37:14.566
I need a minute
to take it all in.

37:14.650 --> 37:16.401
Okay.

37:17.611 --> 37:19.613
I better get going.

37:19.696 --> 37:21.698
Bye.

37:40.342 --> 37:41.927
You know, boys
might come and go,

37:42.010 --> 37:44.930
but a best friend
is once in a lifetime.

37:45.013 --> 37:48.809
We have to hold tight
to our friendships.

37:48.892 --> 37:51.144
Because we never know
what the future will hold.

37:52.145 --> 37:54.147
♪ ♪

37:57.609 --> 37:59.611
[engine starts]

38:19.172 --> 38:20.882
What, did Taylor leave?

38:20.966 --> 38:24.011
Why? Do you want to go
make out with her some more?

38:24.094 --> 38:25.345
Belly, don't give me shit.

38:25.429 --> 38:26.555
All right? I feel bad enough.

38:26.638 --> 38:29.808
You should.
She's my best friend.

38:29.891 --> 38:32.769
- And not to mention
traumatizing me...
- Oh, my God.

38:32.853 --> 38:35.188
- I mean, my eyes. I...
- Stop being so immature.

38:39.943 --> 38:42.946
[scoffs] She really likes you.

38:46.450 --> 38:48.452
Yeah, I know.

38:50.495 --> 38:51.997
Look, just...

38:57.669 --> 38:59.546
Can you please...

39:01.548 --> 39:03.383
...please not tell anyone?

39:04.426 --> 39:05.594
You mean Shayla?

39:07.429 --> 39:08.847
Yeah.

39:11.141 --> 39:13.101
Not that you deserve
this right now...

39:15.937 --> 39:17.522
She seems really into you.

39:17.606 --> 39:19.274
I don't...

39:19.357 --> 39:20.984
I don't know, I just feel like

39:21.068 --> 39:22.652
she's used to being
with, like...

39:24.029 --> 39:25.447
...you know, like,
the kind of guys

39:25.530 --> 39:27.032
who were at Nicole's party
last night.

39:27.115 --> 39:29.993
Yeah, but weren't you a guy
at Nicole's party last night?

39:30.077 --> 39:34.539
I guess I mean she's used to...
guys who treat her like a queen.

39:40.087 --> 39:41.922
You know?
And I don't got it like that.

39:43.632 --> 39:46.384
So, you were feeling insecure,

39:46.468 --> 39:48.929
and that's why you hooked up
with my best friend?

39:49.012 --> 39:50.931
Uh, yeah.

39:53.517 --> 39:55.435
Yeah, I guess.

39:55.519 --> 39:57.813
[♪ Bon Iver: "Beach Baby"]

40:01.399 --> 40:04.569
♪ When you're out,
tell your lucky one ♪

40:08.949 --> 40:12.327
♪ To know that you'll leave ♪

40:15.497 --> 40:18.667
♪ Don't you lock
when you're fleeing ♪

40:20.794 --> 40:22.712
♪ I'd like not...

40:22.796 --> 40:25.465
[Belly] I've wished for Conrad
on every birthday,

40:25.549 --> 40:28.760
every shooting star,
every penny in a fountain.

40:30.762 --> 40:33.765
What if now I have the power
to make my wish come true?

40:35.142 --> 40:37.144
Is Conrad still my wish?

40:46.570 --> 40:48.446
[Susannah laughs] I know.

40:48.530 --> 40:49.739
[both laugh]

40:52.075 --> 40:54.911
Um, I was doing
some research last night.

40:54.995 --> 40:57.330
For your next book?

40:57.414 --> 40:59.749
I was looking
into alternative therapies.

40:59.833 --> 41:04.212
Apparently, a lot has changed
in the last three years.

41:04.296 --> 41:05.922
Have you been speaking to Adam?

41:07.007 --> 41:09.134
I know you said you didn't
want to do chemo, but...

41:09.217 --> 41:10.969
I'm not putting myself
through treatment again.

41:12.470 --> 41:13.763
I know how much time
I have left.

41:13.847 --> 41:15.056
Beck...

41:15.140 --> 41:16.308
No, it's okay.

41:18.310 --> 41:19.644
I'm at peace with it.

41:21.646 --> 41:24.941
I'm gonna tell the kids
when we get back to Boston.

41:27.360 --> 41:32.115
I just want one last
perfect summer at Cousins.

41:32.199 --> 41:34.034
That's all I want.

41:36.203 --> 41:37.412
Okay.

41:52.719 --> 41:54.471
♪ Only hold ♪

41:54.554 --> 41:56.890
♪ Till your coffee warms ♪

42:00.644 --> 42:03.980
♪ But don't hurry and speed ♪

42:06.983 --> 42:09.903
♪ Once a time, put a tongue ♪

42:13.073 --> 42:16.076
♪ In your ear on the beach ♪

42:19.454 --> 42:25.293
♪ And you clutched
clicking heels ♪♪

42:28.838 --> 42:31.841
